  "prompt": "How can I delete a Google account from my phone?",
  "response": "To delete a Google account from your phone, follow these steps. Note that these steps may vary slightly depending on your device model and Android version.\n\n### For Android Devices:\n1. **Open Settings**: Open the Settings app on your Android device.\n2. **Accounts**: Scroll down and tap on \"Accounts\" or \"Users & Accounts.\"\n3. **Select Google Account**: Find and select the Google account you want to remove.\n4. **Remove Account**: Tap on \"Remove Account\" at the bottom of the screen. You may have to confirm your action.\n5. **Enter Password**: If prompted, enter your password to verify that you want to remove the account.\n\n### For iPhone:\n1. **Open Settings**: Open the Settings app on your iPhone.\n2. **Mail or Passwords & Accounts**: Scroll down to \"Mail\" and then tap on \"Accounts\" (or directly on \"Passwords & Accounts,\" depending on your iOS version).\n3. **Select Google Account**: Tap on the Google account you want to remove.\n4. **Delete Account**: Tap on \"Delete Account\" at the bottom, then confirm your action.\n\n### Notes:\n- Removing your Google account will delete all associated data from your device, such as emails, contacts, and calendar events linked to that account.\n- If you have multiple Google accounts and want to just sign out of one, consider just removing the account from the specific app (like Gmail) instead.\n- If you plan to remove your account entirely from Google, rather than just from your device, you'll need to follow steps on a computer or a browser to delete the account permanently, which is a different process.\n\nIf you have further questions or need specific help for a certain device, feel free to ask!",
